<subSubSection id="00BB12ACFFC45777FF44E457FD92CA58" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="481E4127FFC45777FF44E457FCCDCA38" blockId="3.[192,1441,1122,1306]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC45777FF44E457FEEFCB58" bold="true" box="[192,349,1122,1146]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Discussion.</emphasis>
This species is widely distributed in the Neotropics and was previously known from 
<collectingCountry id="30B601B7FFC45777FAC9E457FF4FCBB8" name="Guatemala" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="30B601B7FFC45777FEBFE4B7FE37CBB8" box="[315,389,1154,1178]" name="Belize" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Belize</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="30B601B7FFC45777FE2BE4B6FDA1CBB8" box="[431,531,1155,1178]" name="Panama" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2C303CD6FFC45777FDA1E4B7FCC2CBB8" author="Borkent, A. &amp; G. R. Spinelli" box="[549,880,1154,1178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref13052" refString="Borkent, A., and G. R. Spinelli. 2000. Catalog of the new world biting midges south of the United States of America (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Contributions on Entomology, International 4: 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="2000">Borkent and Spinelli 2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2C303CD6FFC45777FCF8E4B7FC0ECBB8" author="Borkent, A. &amp; G. R. Spinelli" box="[892,956,1154,1178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref13097" refString="Borkent, A., and G. R. Spinelli. 2007. Neotropical Ceratopogonidae (Diptera: Insecta). In: J. Adis, J. R. Arias, G. Rueda-Delgado, and K. M. Wantzen (eds). Aquatic biodiversity in Latin America (ABLA). Vol. 4. Pensoft; Sofia-Moscow. 198 p." type="book" year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
). Two other very similar species in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="8FA13AA4FFC45777FEBDE496FE62CB98" authority="Fox" authorityName="Fox" box="[313,464,1187,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Avaritia">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC45777FEBDE496FE2DCB98" box="[313,415,1187,1210]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Avaritia</emphasis>
Fox
</taxonomicName>
also occur in 
<collectingCountry id="30B601B7FFC45777FDF6E497FD7ECB98" box="[626,716,1186,1210]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8FA13AA4FFC45777FD51E496FC26CB98" authority="Lutz" authorityName="Lutz" authorityYear="1913" box="[725,916,1186,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC45777FD51E496FD5ACB98" box="[725,744,1187,1210]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC45777FD70E497FCE4CB98" box="[756,854,1186,1210]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">pusillus</emphasis>
Lutz
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8FA13AA4FFC45777FC49E496FAAFCB98" authority="Wirth and Mullens." authorityName="Wirth and Mullens." box="[973,1309,1186,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boydi">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC45777FC49E496FC52CB98" box="[973,992,1187,1210]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC45777FC68E497FB9FCB98" box="[1004,1069,1186,1210]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">boydi</emphasis>
Wirth and Mullens.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="8FA13AA4FFC45777FAA6E497FEF5CBF9" authorityName=": Wirth" authorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusilloides">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC45777FAA6E497FA12CB98" box="[1314,1440,1186,1210]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Culicoides</emphasis>
pusilloides
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="8FA13AA4FFC45777FE67E4F6FDF7CBF8" box="[483,581,1218,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boydi">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC45777FE67E4F6FE44CBF8" box="[483,502,1219,1242]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC45777FD80E4F7FDF7CBF8" box="[516,581,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">boydi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the 2 
<superScript id="BFD4EC6FFFC45777FD2BE4F4FD73CBED" attach="left" box="[687,705,1217,1231]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">nd</superScript>
radial cell that is distinctly pale on its apical half, a shorter proboscis (Proboscis/Head ratio 0.50) and the short, broad aedeagus with sides strongly bowed outward. We provide the first records of 
<taxonomicName id="8FA13AA4FFC45777FDB0E536FD6ACA38" authorityName=": Wirth" authorityYear="1974" box="[564,728,1282,1306]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusilloides">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC45777FDB0E536FDF5CA38" box="[564,583,1283,1306]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC45777FDD0E537FD6ACA38" box="[596,728,1282,1306]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">pusilloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="30B601B7FFC45777FC9BE537FCC9CA38" box="[799,891,1282,1306]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="481E4127FFC45777FF44E577FD92CA58" blockId="3.[192,1440,1346,1402]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
